⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Ridley
node MET · MET · ⟦Ridley:MET:3d54fa⟧

WHO   — Ridley — the dragon
WHAT  — A fearsome flying reptilian warlord and recurring boss — a general of cruelty and cleverness who commands the Pirate war machine across Zebes, and who in Super Metroid steals the last baby Metroid from the hunter's hands.
WHERE — MET · Metroid  Framework inputs: Metroid (1986) & Super Metroid (1994)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because conquest and slaughter are his nature; because the Metroids are weapons he and the Pirates would wield to bend the galaxy; and because every torment he visits on Samus is one more cruelty he savors.
HOW   — By wing and claw and fire — a swooping, lashing predator who fights from the air, by the armies and machinery of the Space Pirates, and by a malice sharp enough to make him their general and not merely their beast.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I took your world and your kin, hunter — and I will take whatever you carry out of the dark.

